The paper discusses action recognition using neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on improving the robustness and generalization ability of the models, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper deals with video data (cs.MM) and proposes a new approach for multi-task learning (cs.NE).
